---
import LegalDocument from '../../../components/LegalDocument.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { appLegalProfiles } from '../../../data/appLegalProfiles';
import type { AppLegalProfile } from '../../../data/appLegalProfiles';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return appLegalProfiles.map((profile) => ({
    params: { slug: profile.slug },
    props: { profile },
  }));
}

interface Props {
  profile: AppLegalProfile;
}

const { profile } = Astro.props;
const privacyUrl = `/apps/${profile.slug}/privacy-policy/`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${profile.name} End User License Agreement`}
  description={`End User License Agreement for ${profile.name}.`}
>
  <LegalDocument
    overline={profile.name}
    title="End User License Agreement"
    description={`This End User License Agreement governs access to and use of ${profile.name}, ${profile.appDescription}`}
    effectiveDate={profile.effectiveDate}
  >
    <p>
      This End User License Agreement ("Agreement") is between {profile.legalProvider} ("we," "us," or "our") and the person or organization that accesses or uses {profile.name} (the "App"). If you use the App on behalf of a company or other organization, "you" means both you and that organization, and you represent that you are authorized to accept this Agreement for that organization.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you have a separate written agreement with us for the App, that written agreement controls if it conflicts with this Agreement.
    </p>

    <h2>1. The App</h2>
    <p>
      {profile.name} is {profile.appDescription} The App may connect to QuickBooks Online and other systems that you authorize. The App is not provided by Intuit, and Intuit is not responsible for the App. QuickBooks and Intuit are third-party services and trademarks of Intuit Inc.
    </p>
    <p>
      The App is an internal workflow and reporting tool. Reports generated by the App may be provided to end users or other recipients only as authorized by you or your organization. The App does not provide legal, tax, accounting, investment, or financial advice. You are responsible for reviewing outputs before use or distribution, making business decisions, and consulting qualified professionals when needed.
    </p>

    <h2>2. License</h2>
    <p>
      Subject to this Agreement, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to access and use the App for your internal business purposes. You may allow your employees, contractors, and other authorized users to use the App on your behalf, but you remain responsible for their use.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Accounts and Authorization</h2>
    <p>
      You are responsible for the accuracy of information you provide, for keeping account credentials secure, and for all activity under your account. You may only connect QuickBooks Online companies, files, accounts, and other systems that you are authorized to access. You may revoke the App's QuickBooks Online access through Intuit account settings or by contacting us.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Customer Data</h2>
    <p>
      You retain ownership of data that you or your authorized systems submit to the App, including QuickBooks Online data ("Customer Data"). You grant us the rights needed to host, process, transmit, display, and otherwise use Customer Data to provide, secure, support, and improve the App, and to comply with law.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are responsible for obtaining all permissions and notices required for Customer Data that you provide, authorize us to access, or include in reports sent to end users. Our handling of personal information and QuickBooks Online data is described in the <a href={privacyUrl}>Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Restrictions</h2>
    <p>You may not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>use the App for unlawful, deceptive, harmful, or infringing activity;</li>
      <li>copy, modify, reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code from the App except to the extent allowed by law;</li>
      <li>interfere with or disrupt the App, its security, or its infrastructure;</li>
      <li>use automated scraping, load testing, or similar activity without our written permission;</li>
      <li>sell, sublicense, rent, lease, or provide the App to third parties except as expressly permitted by us;</li>
      <li>send reports or Customer Data to recipients who are not authorized to receive them;</li>
      <li>submit malicious code or content that violates the rights of others; or</li>
      <li>use the App to build or benchmark a competing service without our written permission.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Fees</h2>
    <p>
      Fees, payment terms, subscriptions, implementation charges, or other commercial terms may be stated in an order form, statement of work, invoice, or other written agreement. Unless a separate written agreement says otherwise, fees are non-refundable to the maximum extent permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Support, Changes, and Availability</h2>
    <p>
      We may provide support through the contact method listed below or through another support process we make available. We may update, modify, suspend, or discontinue all or part of the App. We will use commercially reasonable efforts to avoid unnecessary disruption, but we do not guarantee that the App will be uninterrupted, error-free, or available at all times.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      The App may rely on third-party services, including QuickBooks Online, hosting providers, email providers, analytics providers, and other software services. Your use of third-party services is governed by their terms and policies. We are not responsible for third-party services or changes to those services.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Confidentiality</h2>
    <p>
      Each party may receive non-public information from the other party. The receiving party will use reasonable care to protect confidential information and will use it only as needed to perform under this Agreement, unless disclosure is required by law or authorized by the disclosing party.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      We and our licensors retain all rights, title, and interest in the App, including software, designs, workflows, documentation, and other materials. No rights are granted except as expressly stated in this Agreement. Feedback you provide may be used by us without restriction or obligation to you.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the App is provided "as is" and "as available." We disclaim all warranties, whether express, implied, statutory, or otherwise, including implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, title, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that App outputs will be complete, accurate, or suitable for your particular business decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, neither party will be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for lost profits, lost revenues, lost goodwill, business interruption, or loss of data. To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability for all claims relating to the App will not exceed the greater of the amounts you paid us for the App in the twelve months before the event giving rise to the claim or one hundred dollars (US $100).
    </p>

    <h2>13. Indemnity</h2>
    <p>
      You will defend, indemnify, and hold us harmless from claims, damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses arising from your use of the App, your Customer Data, your violation of this Agreement, or your violation of law or third-party rights.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Suspension and Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You may stop using the App at any time. We may suspend or terminate access if you violate this Agreement, if required by law or a third-party platform, if your use creates security or operational risk, or if the App is discontinued. Upon termination, your license ends and you must stop using the App. Sections that by their nature should survive will survive, including ownership, confidentiality, disclaimers, limitations of liability, indemnity, and governing law.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Governing Law</h2>
    <p>
      This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Florida, excluding its conflict-of-law rules. The state and federal courts located in Florida will have exclusive jurisdiction for disputes arising from this Agreement, unless a separate written agreement states otherwise.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Changes to this Agreement</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Agreement from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the effective date above and provide notice when required. Continued use of the App after an update means you accept the updated Agreement.
    </p>

    <h2>17. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this Agreement can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${profile.contactEmail}`}>{profile.contactEmail}</a>. {profile.legalProvider} is based in {profile.location}.
    </p>
  </LegalDocument>
</BaseLayout>
